- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper involves developing a computational framework for predicting the future behavior of blocked users, which could potentially involve complex algorithms and security considerations. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a less likely but possible category as the paper may involve developing software tools or techniques for community moderation and management.
